Day 4 – HTML Lists

Lists organize related data clearly.
There are three types of lists:

Ordered List (<ol>) – numbered items.

Unordered List (<ul>) – bullet points.

Description List (<dl>) – term and description pairs.
Example:

<ul>
  <li>HTML</li>
  <li>CSS</li>
  <li>JavaScript</li>
</ul>


Lists make information structured and easy to read.
